
@startuml

' Define classes
class City {
  - name: String
  - inhabitants: int
}

class Attraction {
  - name: String
  - address: String
}

class GuidedTour {
  - duration: int
  - tourNumber: int
  - maxVisitors: int = 20
}

class Discount {
  - amount: double
}

class Guide {
  - name: String
}

class Visitor {
  - name: String
}

class Person {
  - name: String
}

' Relationships
City "1" -- "many" Attraction : has
Attraction "1" -- "many" GuidedTour : offers
GuidedTour "1" -- "1" Guide : requires
GuidedTour "1" -- "many" Visitor : participates in
GuidedTour "1" -- "many" Discount : may have
Visitor --|> Person
Guide --|> Person

@enduml

### Explanation of the Diagram:
- **City** contains multiple **Attractions**.
- Each **Attraction** can offer multiple **GuidedTours**.
- A **GuidedTour** has a maximum of 20 **Visitors**, and each tour must have one **Guide**.
- **Discounts** are optional and can be applied to certain **GuidedTours**.
- Both **Visitor** and **Guide** inherit from the **Person** class, as they are both people with names.

